# Cursor/AI Agent Rules for OpenState

## Project Architecture Constraints

### Mandatory Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 16.1.3 App Router ONLY (no Pages Router)
- **React**: 19.2.3 with React Compiler enabled
- **TypeScript**: 5.9.3 strict mode
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS 3.4.1 with GovApple design tokens
- **Backend**: Python 3.x scripts (no Node.js backend)
- **Data**: PostgreSQL database with Drizzle ORM (Legacy JSON files removed)
12: - **DB Migrations**: Drizzle-kit for schema management

### Forbidden Patterns
❌ **DO NOT**:
- Use Next.js Pages Router
- Use state management libraries (Redux, Zustand) - use React built-ins
- Hardcode database connection strings (use `.env`)
- Disable TypeScript strict mode
- Use inline styles (use Tailwind utilities)
- Hardcode data (must come from database)
- Create new Python web frameworks (Flask, FastAPI) - keep scripts only

---

## Coding Standards

### File Naming Conventions
```
frontend/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx              # Route pages (lowercase)
│   ├── layout.tsx            # Layouts
│   └── [id]/                 # Dynamic routes (lowercase)
│       └── ComponentName.tsx # Components (PascalCase)
├── components/
│   └── ComponentName.tsx     # PascalCase for components
└── lib/
    └── utilityName.ts        # camelCase for utilities

backend/
├── fetch_*.py                # Snake_case for scripts
└── parsers/
    └── module_name.py        # Snake_case for modules
```

### TypeScript Rules
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Explicit typing for all exported functions
export async function getProcesses(): Promise<LegislativeProcess[]> {
  // ...
}

// ❌ WRONG: No implicit any
export async function getProcesses() {  // Missing return type
  // ...
}

// ✅ CORRECT: Interface for all data structures
export interface LegislativeProcess {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  kanbanStage?: string; // Optional fields marked
}

// ❌ WRONG: Using 'type' for data structures (use interface)
export type LegislativeProcess = { /* ... */ }
```

### React Component Rules
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Server Component (default)
export default async function BillPage({ params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }) {
  const { id } = await params;
  const bill = await getBill(id);
  return <div>{bill.title}</div>;
}

// ✅ CORRECT: Client Component (when needed)
"use client";
import { useState } from "react";

export default function InteractiveList() {
  const [filter, setFilter] = useState("");
  // ... interactive logic
}

// ❌ WRONG: Mixing server and client without "use client"
import { useState } from "react"; // ERROR: can't use hooks in Server Component
export default function BadComponent() { /* ... */ }
```

### Tailwind Usage
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Use design tokens from tailwind.config.js
<div className="bg-apple-blue text-white rounded-card shadow-apple-lg">

// ✅ CORRECT: Use utility classes
<div className="card-apple p-6">  {/* card-apple from globals.css */}

// ❌ WRONG: Arbitrary values without good reason
<div className="bg-[#007AFF]">  {/* Use bg-apple-blue instead */}

// ✅ CORRECT: Dark mode
<p className="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300">

// ❌ WRONG: Hardcoded colors
<p className="text-gray-300">  {/* Unreadable in light mode */}
```

