## Error Handling & Edge Cases

### Missing Data Handling
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Graceful degradation
const description = process.description || "No description available";
const isapLink = process.isapLink ? <a href={process.isapLink}>...</a> : null;

// ✅ CORRECT: useEffect cleanup to prevent refresh loops
useEffect(() => {
  let mounted = true;
  fetch('/data/file.json')
    .then(res => {
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Not found');
      return res.json();
    })
    .then(data => {
      if (mounted) setState(data);
    })
    .catch(err => {
      if (mounted) console.warn('Data unavailable', err);
    });
  return () => { mounted = false; };
}, [dependency]);

// ❌ WRONG: No cleanup = memory leaks and refresh loops
useEffect(() => {
  fetch('/data/file.json').then(res => setState(res.json()));
}, []);
```

### Dark Mode Compliance
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Every text color must have dark variant
<p className="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300">

// ❌ WRONG: Hardcoded light-only color
<p className="text-gray-300">  {/* Invisible on white background */}

// ✅ CORRECT: Backgrounds also need dark variants
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
```

